                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Dino,<br /><br />There is a fair mix of living and undead (and a couple see invis) mobs in AR.  Also there are plenty of traps.<br /><br />I have absolutely no problem getting anywhere I need to go in AR (even got to Shei t'other day with only skin like shadow) but expect to need to FD when you hit traps or have to get past an undead or see-invis mob.  All of the traps will despawn (and of course you have a window where you don't have to worry about re-triggering it...30 mins I think?) after a while and so you can get up safely and recast Force Shield / Skin like shadow and move on from there...<br /><br />The biggest danger, IMO, to getting to the altar are the (rare and apparently random) traps that spawn several mind worms...they not only interrupt you like crazy but also suck on your mana.  Between Virtue and Force Shield I don't recall ever dying to them, however.  Just remember to target one of the trap mobs so you can see when it despawns and therefore it's safe to get back up.<br /><br />Hope I was clear enough in the above...I feel like I'm trying to convey too much info in too few words =P...long as you're careful, it should be a walk in the park getting to the altar without engaging (but with no fewer than 3 fd's) a single mob.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><hr noshade size="1"><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <img src="http://home.comcast.net/~topknot/wsb/media/350795/site1015.jpg" border="0"><br />Arch Lich <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592061" target="_blank">Sthythys Sthythophilous</a><br />The Lizardly Lich of <a href="http://www.savagearms.org" target="_blank">Savage Arms</a></span></font></td>
